---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import { APP_STORE_URL, isAppStoreUrlKnown, SITE_NAME, getCampaignAppStoreUrl } from '../../lib/site';

const campaignToken = 'seo_en_taper';
const appStoreKnown = isAppStoreUrlKnown(APP_STORE_URL);
const appStoreCtaLabel = appStoreKnown ? 'Download on the App Store' : 'Coming soon on the App Store';
const finalAppStoreUrl = getCampaignAppStoreUrl(campaignToken);
---

<Layout
	title="Taper Nicotine Gradually — Calm Reduction App | Wean Nicotine"
	description="Wean Nicotine helps you reduce nicotine gradually with a daily allowance that decreases week by week. Track your use, handle cravings, and see progress over time."
	canonicalPath="/taper-nicotine/"
	availableLocales={['en']}
>
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<h1>Taper nicotine gradually with a calm, private app</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				Wean Nicotine is an iPhone app that tapers your nicotine intake by reducing your daily pouch allowance by 5% each week by default — so you cut down gradually instead of quitting cold turkey.
				Gradual reduction has been shown to be as effective as abrupt cessation for long-term quit success (Lindson et al., Cochrane Review 2019). Log each pouch in one tap (under 2 seconds) and lower your use at a pace that works for you.
			</p>
			<div class="cta">
				<Button variant="primary" href={finalAppStoreUrl} disabled={!appStoreKnown} external={true}>
					{appStoreCtaLabel}
				</Button>
				<Button variant="secondary" href="/">Learn more about Wean Nicotine</Button>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<Section id="who" title="Who nicotine tapering is for" lede="Gradual reduction works well for people who find cold turkey too abrupt.">
		<div class="grid-2">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>You want to cut down, not stop all at once</h3>
				<p>Tapering means reducing your daily use over weeks. The average snus or nicotine pouch user consumes 10 to 15 pouches per day, and a 5% weekly step-down is gentle enough that your body adjusts without the intense withdrawal of an abrupt stop.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>You use snus or nicotine pouches daily</h3>
				<p>Whether you use snus, ZYN, VELO, or other nicotine pouches, Wean Nicotine works with any daily pouch routine. Just set your starting number.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Cold turkey has not worked for you</h3>
				<p>Many people try to quit overnight and end up back at their old level within days. Research shows gradual reduction is as effective as abrupt cessation for long-term success (Lindson et al., Cochrane Review 2019). A gradual approach gives your body time to adjust.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>You want a clear plan</h3>
				<p>Wean Nicotine gives you a specific daily number instead of a vague goal. You always know exactly how many pouches you have left today.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</Section>

	<Section id="how" title="How nicotine tapering works in Wean Nicotine" lede="A simple three-step process that adjusts automatically.">
		<div class="grid-3">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>1) Enter your current use</h3>
				<p>Tell Wean how many pouches you use per day. This is your starting point. No judgment, just an honest number.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>2) Follow a decreasing allowance</h3>
				<p>Each week your daily allowance goes down by a percentage you choose — 5% by default. Log each pouch in one tap (the average session takes under 2 seconds) throughout the day.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>3) Use support tools when cravings hit</h3>
				<p>Breathing exercises, urge surfing, and reflection prompts are built in. They help you get through the moments when you want to reach for a pouch.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</Section>

	<Section id="why" title="Why gradual nicotine tapering works" lede="Research and experience suggest that reducing gradually can be more sustainable than stopping abruptly.">
		<div class="grid-2">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Milder withdrawal</h3>
				<p>By reducing slowly, your body adjusts to lower nicotine levels without the intense withdrawal symptoms that come from quitting all at once. Nicotine cravings typically peak within 3 to 5 minutes and then subside, and a gradual taper keeps those peaks smaller.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Builds lasting habits</h3>
				<p>Each week at a lower level reinforces new patterns. Over time, using fewer pouches becomes your new normal.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Less risk of relapse</h3>
				<p>People who reduce gradually are less likely to bounce back to their original use compared to those who quit abruptly and then restart. Self-monitoring — simply tracking your use — can reduce consumption by 15 to 20% even without a formal plan (Burke et al., Journal of the American Dietetic Association).</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>You stay in control</h3>
				<p>Wean Nicotine reduces your allowance by 5% each week. If the plan is not working for you, the Start Over flow lets you restart with a new baseline. The goal is steady progress, not perfection.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</Section>

	<Section id="faq" title="Frequently asked questions about nicotine tapering">
		<div class="grid-2">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>How fast should I taper nicotine?</h3>
				<p>Most people reduce by 5 to 15 percent per week. Wean Nicotine uses a 5% weekly reduction — gentle enough for your body to adjust without severe withdrawal.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Does Wean Nicotine work for all nicotine products?</h3>
				<p>Wean Nicotine is built for snus and nicotine pouches. If you use pouches daily and want to cut down, it is designed for you. Learn more about <a href="/snus-reduction-app/">snus reduction</a> or <a href="/nicotine-pouch-reduction-app/">nicotine pouch reduction</a>.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>What if I have a bad day?</h3>
				<p>Going over your allowance does not reset your progress. Wean Nicotine tracks what happened and moves forward. One bad day is not failure.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Is my data private?</h3>
				<p>Yes. Your usage data is stored on your iPhone — no cloud sync, no account required, and no third-party usage analytics. It is a one-time purchase for 29 DKK (approximately $4 USD). Read more about <a href="/private-quit-nicotine-app/">how Wean Nicotine protects your privacy</a>.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</Section>

	<script type="application/ld+json">
		{
			"@context": "https://schema.org",
			"@type": "BreadcrumbList",
			"itemListElement": [
				{
					"@type": "ListItem",
					"position": 1,
					"name": "Home",
					"item": "https://weannicotine.iamjarl.com"
				},
				{
					"@type": "ListItem",
					"position": 2,
					"name": "Taper Nicotine",
					"item": "https://weannicotine.iamjarl.com/taper-nicotine/"
				}
			]
		}
	</script>

	<section class="bottom-cta">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Ready to taper your nicotine use?</h2>
			<p>Start with your current daily amount and let Wean Nicotine guide you down gradually.</p>
			<Button variant="primary" href={finalAppStoreUrl} disabled={!appStoreKnown} external={true}>
				{appStoreCtaLabel}
			</Button>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.hero {
		padding: clamp(54px, 7vw, 96px) 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
	}

	h1 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
		font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 48px);
		line-height: 1.1;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	}

	.lede {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		max-width: 62ch;
		font-size: 18px;
		line-height: 28px;
	}

	.cta {
		display: flex;
		gap: var(--space-md);
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.grid-2, .grid-3 {
		display: grid;
		gap: var(--space-lg);
	}

	.grid-2 { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
	.grid-3 { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); }

	h3 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
		font-size: 18px;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
	}

	p { margin: 0; color: var(--text-secondary); }

	.bottom-cta {
		padding: clamp(44px, 6vw, 84px) 0;
		text-align: center;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
	}

	.bottom-cta h2 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
		font-size: clamp(28px, 3.2vw, 36px);
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.bottom-cta p {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
		color: var(--text-secondary);
	}

	@media (max-width: 960px) {
		.grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
	}

	@media (max-width: 700px) {
		.grid-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
	}
</style>
